TITLE: Gap stock slides 18% after cutting sales guidance; CEO of Old Navy division to leave
SUMMARY: A snarled supply chain has been particularly hard on its Old Navy division, which targets a lower-income consumer.

TITLE: Snap reports ‘challenging’ quarter that missed sales and profit estimates
SUMMARY: Snap reported first-quarter results on Thursday after the bell.

TITLE: American forecasts second-quarter profit on soaring travel demand, airline stocks rally
SUMMARY: American expects to fly as much as 94% of its 2019 second-quarter schedule, more than competitors Delta Air Lines and United Airlines.

TITLE: Tesla reports $18.76 billion in revenue and record margins in Q1
SUMMARY: Revenue growth was driven in part by an increase in the number of cars Tesla delivered, and an increase in average sales prices

TITLE: United forecasts a 2022 profit as passengers return and pay more to fly
SUMMARY: United says strong demand and higher fares are allowing the airline to cover its fuel costs.

TITLE: Procter & Gamble tops Wall Street estimates as price hikes counteract higher costs
SUMMARY: Consumer goods giant P&G may serve as a bellwether for investors as costs rise and shoppers weigh higher price tags.

TITLE: Netflix shares crater 25% after company reports it lost subscribers for the first time in more than 10 years
SUMMARY: It's the first time the streamer has reported a subscriber loss in more than a decade.

TITLE: IBM first-quarter results beat estimates
SUMMARY: IBM sees growth in 2022 after the company spun off its managed-infrastructure services unit.

TITLE: J&J lowers 2022 revenue and earnings expectations, stops giving Covid vaccine sales guidance
SUMMARY: When asked about halting guidance for J&J's Covid vaccine, CFO Joe Wolk said the shots are not for profit and do not impact the company's bottom line.

TITLE: Bank of America shares jump after lender tops analysts' estimates on better-than-expected credit
SUMMARY: Bank of America's moves are in contrast to rival JPMorgan Chase, which disclosed last week that it took a $1.46 billion provision for credit losses.

TITLE: Morgan Stanley earnings top estimates fueled by trading revenue gains
SUMMARY: Morgan Stanley saw stronger-than-expected revenue from equity and fixed-income trading amid volatile markets.

TITLE: Wells Fargo shares fall as quarterly revenue misses estimates on weaker-than-expected mortgage lending
SUMMARY: Wells Fargo on Thursday reported lower-than-expected first-quarter revenue amid a drop in mortgage lending.

TITLE: Citigroup tops earnings estimates on better-than-expected trading revenue
SUMMARY: Citigroup topped first-quarter profit and revenue estimates helped by better-than-expected trading results.

TITLE: Goldman Sachs tops analyst estimates as trading desks crush expectations amid surging volatility
SUMMARY: Goldman seems to have exceeded other Wall Street firms in benefiting from the sudden market upheaval caused by the Ukraine conflict.

TITLE: Rent the Runway CEO sees inflation as a competitive advantage for the company
SUMMARY: On Wednesday, the fashion rental platform reported fiscal fourth-quarter revenue ahead of analysts' estimates along with a narrower-than-expected loss.

TITLE: Bed Bath & Beyond warns of slowing consumer demand after posting weak holiday-quarter results
SUMMARY: Bed Bath & Beyond is in the middle of a turnaround effort and has been under pressure from an activist investor.

TITLE: Delta forecasts a quarterly profit as travelers keep flying despite higher fares, helping offset surging fuel costs
SUMMARY: Delta said it expects a pretax profit in the second quarter and that it will restore capacity to 84% of 2019 levels.

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase reports $524 million hit from market dislocations caused by Russia sanctions
SUMMARY: JPMorgan said Wednesday that first-quarter profit fell because of increased costs tied to bad loans and market upheaval caused by the Ukraine war.

TITLE: Levi Strauss earnings top estimates as shoppers buy at higher prices, denim retailer reaffirms 2022 outlook
SUMMARY: Levi Strauss sold more of its jeans and T-shirts at higher price points, often directly to consumers.

TITLE: Walgreens shares fall as pandemic demand slows and health-care investments ramp up
SUMMARY: Walgreens, which saw strong sales during the winter quarter, maintained its outlook for the year.

TITLE: Huawei posts first-ever yearly revenue decline as U.S. sanctions continue to bite, but profit surges
SUMMARY: Huawei's business has been hurt by U.S. sanctions, which have sought to cut it off from key software and components like semiconductors.

TITLE: Olive Garden parent's earnings miss estimates, company lowers fiscal 2022 outlook
SUMMARY: Darden Restaurants, which owns Olive Garden, reported quarterly earnings and revenue that missed analysts' expectations.

TITLE: Tencent reports slowest revenue growth on record as China's regulatory headwinds remain
SUMMARY: Tencent reported its slowest quarterly revenue growth on record in the fourth quarter of 2021.

TITLE: Nike reports sales growth driven by North American demand, delays outlook amid global unrest
SUMMARY: Nike said it will provide a more detailed outlook for fiscal 2023 when it reports fourth-quarter results.

TITLE: Saudi Aramco's full-year profit more than doubles on soaring oil prices
SUMMARY: Saudi Arabian oil giant Aramco reported blowout full-year earnings on Sunday, posting a more than doubling in year-on-year net profit to $110 billion.

TITLE: GameStop shares fall as retailer reports loss during holiday quarter, says it will launch NFT marketplace
SUMMARY: The video game retailer's digital-focused moves have yet to translate into profits.

TITLE: Warby Parker offers weak outlook, reports loss from holiday quarter
SUMMARY: Warby Parker said sales were hurt in the final weeks of December, which coincided with typical peak demand in the optical industry.

TITLE: Oracle misses on earnings as investments drag down quarterly profit
SUMMARY: Investments in a gene-sequencing company and a server chip maker cut into Oracle's earnings, which missed analysts' expectations.

TITLE: Stitch Fix shares plummet after company cuts guidance for the year
SUMMARY: Stitch Fix offered a weak outlook for its fiscal third quarter and slashed its forecast for the full year.

TITLE: Dick's Sporting Goods expects more profit momentum after solid holiday quarter
SUMMARY: CEO Lauren Hobart said the company's 2022 outlook establishes a new foundation for the Dick's to build upon in the future.
